<subSubSection id="C32510B5FFF9FFC7B4A2644728A6FF6B" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="4" pageNumber="274" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B80433EFFF9FFC6B4A264472B83F8D6" blockId="4.[151,598,1833,1896]" box="[151,405,1869,1896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">
(
<figureCitation id="13045FBBFFF9FFC6B4AA64472B28F8D9" box="[159,318,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,194,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-15@2.[151,1436,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1, Diablophthalmus. A–B, D. wygodzinskyorum sp. n., male holotype, dorsal and lateral habitus. C–E, D. marmoratus sp. n.: C–D, dorsal and lateral habitus; E, head and thorax in part, anteroventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592752" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592752/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">Figures 1C–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13045FBBFFF9FFC6B57C64472B9AF8D9" box="[329,396,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[153,1429,822,1662]" captionTargetId="figure-215@4.[153,1435,813,1668]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Diablophthalmus female terminalia. A, sternite VII, D. wygodzinskyorum. B, same, D. marmoratus. C–G, D. marmoratus: C, first valvula; D, same, enlarged view of apex. E, second valvulae; F, same, enlarged view of apex. G, gonoplac." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6592756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6592756/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">3B–G</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B80433EFFF9FFC7B4A2649F28A6FF6B" blockId="4.[151,1437,1941,2039]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="275" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">
<emphasis id="B94B9F2CFFF9FFC6B4A2649F2B3FF811" bold="true" box="[151,297,1941,1967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="274">Description.</emphasis>
Length of female 
<quantity id="4CC7EEDBFFF9FFC6B635649F284EF80E" box="[512,600,1941,1968]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="274" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1 mm</quantity>
(male unknown). Overall color reddish brown, forewing margin with alternating bands of white and brown coloration. Head with dorsal projections in dorsal view separated from each other by less than length of each projection; frontal carina well developed, extended continuously between antennal ledges. Pronotum with small median crest posteriorly. Female sternite VII with median posterior notch slightly shallower and broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F38BDFFF8FFC7B58B63B128BFFF6B" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="2022" box="[446,681,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Diablophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wygodzinskyorum">
D. 
<emphasis id="B94B9F2CFFF8FFC7B5D563B128BFFF6B" box="[480,681,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="275">wygodzinskyorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
