<paragraph id="8B80433EFFF8FFC7B4F2622D2AC2FE37" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis id="B94B9F2CFFF8FFC7B4F2622D2B10FEFF" bold="true" box="[199,262,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="275">Note.</emphasis>
Although this species is known only from a single female specimen, it is easily distinguishable from the 
<typeStatus id="5484FD9CFFF8FFC7B4A262412AD1FEDB" box="[151,199,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="275">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus by the smaller size, different coloration, and more closely set dorsal projections of the head.
</paragraph>
